{
  pages:
  [
    "[{\"text\":\"We thought ourselves blessed when the neighboring mining locations went dark and we could ask a premium for what we dug up. This however was short lasted as we came to face the harsh truth of the rumors that had spread around.\"}]",
    "[{\"text\":\"First we thought they were just strong stories, then we thought it was superstitious belief. We happily kept mining and weeks passed by until a particular cold night hit us by surprise after which everything changed.\"}]",
    "[{\"text\":\"The sightings of shadows is what it started with, then the disappearances and eventually the screaming from deep within the mines. It was then when we decided to band up and look for the cause in force... With 14 we went in and only 3 returned.\"}]",
    "[{\"text\":\"I am the only one remaining at the camp as everyone else fled. I just couldn't bear to leave my friends behind and decided to wait a couple more days. This marks the end of day 2 and I fear the worst but I will remain a little while longer for hope still lingers.\"}]"
  ],
  title:"The last resident",
  author:"Chief Mullard",
  display:{Lore:["A dusty, superficially damaged book."]}
}

{
  pages:
  [
    "[{\"text\":\"Stories about rock, rich with minerals and hollow earth is what attracted us to this place and as promised we were met with a wonderous complex of caverns hard to reach due to the thick layers of sharp obsidian.\"}]",
    "[{\"text\":\"hopeful of treasures that would be weighted we dug deeper and deeper until we found ourselves in a glorious chasm of mushrooms and magma.\"}]",
    "[{\"text\":\"Days went by and aside the usual composition of minerals we sadly didnt found anything worth while, at the very least however we've witnessed a glorious wonder of nature.\"}]"
  ],
  title:"Survey of the depth",
  author:"Oleg the Miner",
  display:{Lore:["A description of what lies below."]}
}
